# UI / Templates Rules

Canonical sources (read before any UI work):
1. `knowledge/design/BRAND_GUIDELINES.md` — identity
2. `knowledge/design/UI_UX_IMPLEMENTATION_STANDARD.md` — UX-001 implementation
3. `knowledge/design/UI_GUARDIAN.md` — enforcement / release gate

UI quality is a **release blocker**. Brand guidelines define identity; UX-001 defines tokens and patterns; UI Guardian governs workflow and validation. Do not invent design tokens outside the system.

## Mandatory workflow (before writing UI code)

1. Read Brand Guidelines + UX-001 + UI Guardian.
2. Inspect existing reusable components / partials / CSS tokens.
3. Reuse whenever possible; create new components only when none fit.
4. Verify the proposal against the design system — then implement.

## Never invent

Colours, spacing, typography, button styles, shadows, radii, animations, icons, layouts, component behaviour, responsive rules, or accessibility behaviour. Everything originates from the design system.

## Brand colours (never invent new ones)

| Token | HEX | Role |
|---|---|---|
| Primary Blue | `#3B4FB8` | Primary actions, links, focus, charts |
| Primary Dark | `#0D1B2A` | Text / dark UI |
| Deep Navy | `#0A1628` | Elevated dark chrome |
| Midnight | `#020D24` | Dark canvases |
| Gold | `#E8B02B` | Achievement / logo / awards only |
| White | `#FFFFFF` | Surfaces / contrast |

Gold is **not** a UI colour. Never use gold for buttons, nav, links, focus, or charts. Reject random blues/greys/gradients/accents.

## Tokens (UX-001)

- **Spacing (8-pt):** 4, 8, 12, 16, 24, 32, 48, 64, 96, 128 only.
- **Type:** Inter only. Sizes: page 40 / section 28 / card 20 / body 16 / caption 14.
- **Icons:** Lucide only; 20 / 24 / 32 px; never replace labels.
- **Cards:** 16px radius, large padding, soft shadow, no gradients/decorative fills.
- **Inputs:** 12px radius, visible labels, helper/errors below, blue focus ring; never placeholder-as-label.
- **Buttons:** One dominant Brand Blue CTA; Secondary outlined; Ghost minimal. Hover lift 2px, press scale 98%, 200ms ease-out. No new variants without approval.
- **Motion:** Communicative only — hover/fade/slide/scale. Reject bounce/flash/shake/spin/elastic/long transitions.
- **Charts:** Brand Blue + neutrals; semantic colours only when meaningful.

## Page / hierarchy gate

Answer in under five seconds: What is this page? Most important action? Where should the eye go first? What next? Prefer less content, clearer hierarchy, intentional whitespace. Avoid equal emphasis, competing CTAs, and visual noise.

## States (feature incomplete without them)

Loading · Empty · Success · Failure · Permission denied · Offline (where applicable). Skeleton loaders preferred; calm microcopy (no blame, jargon, or stack traces).

## A11y / responsive / performance

WCAG AA, keyboard, visible focus, ARIA, semantic HTML, large targets — failures block release. Desktop → tablet → mobile: recompose, do not shrink. Avoid layout shift, heavy animation, oversized assets, duplicate libraries.

## Jinja / CSS / JS

```
app/templates/
  layouts/     # base.html, auth_base.html
  partials/    # sidebar, topnav, flash_messages
  <feature>/
```

- Authenticated → `layouts/base.html`; auth → `layouts/auth_base.html`.
- Reuse partials; no screen-local design systems. Business rules stay in services.
- CSS: `app/static/css/app.css` (+ `wizard.css` via `extra_head`). Bootstrap 5.3 via CDN — no second framework without milestone approval.
- JS: `app/static/js/app.js` + feature files; CSRF from `<meta name="csrf-token">`; progressive enhancement; respect CSP.

## Release gate (UI Guardian)

Not complete until Brand + UX-001 + Guardian + a11y + responsive + performance pass. Self-review: Would Apple remove / Linear simplify / Notion make this easier to scan? If yes — implement the simpler solution.
